# Code of Conduct

## 1. Purpose

The "Missing Child and Criminal Detection System using OpenCV" project is committed to providing a safe, respectful, and inclusive environment for all contributors, regardless of their background, identity, or experience. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for all participants in our community.

## 2. Expected Behavior

All contributors are expected to:

- Be respectful and considerate of others' opinions and ideas.
- Use welcoming and inclusive language and tone.
- Show empathy towards other community members.
- Be open to constructive criticism and feedback.
- Respect and appreciate the diversity of backgrounds and perspectives within the community.
- Address conflicts and disagreements in a respectful and constructive manner.

## 3. Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are considered unacceptable within our community:

- Harassment, discrimination, or any form of offensive, disrespectful, or inappropriate conduct.
- Any form of verbal, physical, or online abuse, trolling, or harassment.
- Discrimination or exclusion based on race, gender, sexual orientation, disability, religion, or any other personal characteristic.
- Invasion of privacy, including sharing personal information without consent.
- Any other behavior that creates an unsafe or unwelcoming environment for others.

## 4. Reporting and Enforcement

If you witness or experience any unacceptable behavior within the project's community, please report it to the project maintainers at [jayanthsct@gmail.com]. All reports will be treated confidentially and will be reviewed and investigated promptly.

Project maintainers are responsible for enforcing the Code of Conduct. If a participant engages in unacceptable behavior, the maintainers may take appropriate action, which may include a warning, temporary or permanent expulsion from the community, or other actions they deem necessary.

## 5. Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org), version 2.0, available at [https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/0/code_of_conduct.html).

## 6. Contact Information

If you have any questions or concerns about this Code of Conduct or its enforcement, please contact the project maintainers at [jayanthsct@gmail.com].

